────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. DEFINITIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

"Platform Code" means the core governance runtime and associated files that are
inherited unmodified in every customer deployment, including but not limited to:
  - app.py (governance runtime)
  - backend-ui-bridge/ (UI bridge service)
  - Frontend/ (React UI)
  - docker-compose.yml (base compose configuration)
  - requirements.txt and pyproject.toml
  - openapi.yaml
  - contracts/business-profiles/ (existing sector profile schemas)
  - contracts/keys/ (existing signing key configuration)
  - deploy/kubernetes/ (base Kubernetes manifests)

"Customer Instance" means a fork of the Platform Code repository, provisioned
by Vendorlogic for a named Customer, containing Customer-specific configuration
layered on top of the unmodified Platform Code.

"Customer Configuration" means files added exclusively within a Customer Instance
that do not modify Platform Code, including:
  - customer-config/<customer-name>/ (environment variables, secret manifests)
  - docker-compose.staging.yml (environment-specific compose overrides)
  - scripts/pull-keyvault-secrets.sh and .ps1 (Key Vault integration scripts)
  - New sector profile JSON files added under contracts/business-profiles/
  - New signing public keys added under contracts/keys/

"Subscription Agreement" means the executed commercial agreement between
Vendorlogic and the Customer governing the licensing, support, and use of
the Software.

